(5,1), (1,3)\;\text{and}\;(-1,-2)
f_1(x) = \frac{5x+1}{2}
f_2(x) = \frac{7-x}{2}
f_3(x)= \frac{x-3}{2}
(-1,f_1(-1)) = (-1,f_3(-1)) = (-1,-2)
(1,f_1(1)) = (1,f_2(1)) = (1,3)
(5,f_2(5)) = (5, f_3(5)) = (5, 1)
A = \int_{-1}^1 (f_1(x)-f_3(x) ) dx + \int_{1}^5 (f_2(x)-f_3(x) ) dx = 4 +8 = 12
